A man was on Monday charged with attempting to commit suicide while in police custody contrary to the law. Boniface Kagondu was charged before Kibera chief magistrate Abdul Loroto where he denied the charges. Kagondu, committed the offence on August 16 in Eastleigh police cells in Kamukunji sub-county within Nairobi County. He was also charged with creating disturbances by threatening to kill Jenifer Kavete Mutuku by using his fist. He however denied the charges and told court that there was no way he could commit suicide. The magistrate released him on Sh5,000 cash bail and directed the matter to be mentioned on August 31.